Benefits of Your Raw Data Approach:
✅ Minimal API Calls: Only 3 endpoints for raw sheet data
✅ Maximum Flexibility: All filtering, date ranges, parameters handled client-side
✅ Better Performance: Raw data cached, no repeated API calls for different parameters
✅ Real-time Filtering: Users can change date ranges, filters without API delays
✅ Reduced Server Load: Google Apps Script just exports raw data, no complex calculations

Implementation Strategy:
1. Google Apps Script - Raw Data Endpoints
2. Static Data Sync - Raw Sheets
3. Client-Side Processing Hooks
4. Updated Component Usage
Migration Plan:
Add raw data endpoints to GoogleScript.gs
Update data sync to fetch raw sheets instead of computed stats
Create calculation utilities for client-side processing
Update hooks to use raw data + client-side calculations
Add filtering components for date ranges, players, etc.
This approach transforms your app from "request → wait → display" to "filter → calculate → display instantly"!

